> <@jackworks:matrix.org> All I know is, if you try to reuse it in Rust, it will be rejected by the compiler ðŸ˜‚
> 
> ```rust
> fn main() {
>    let a = (1..5).into_iter();
>    //   for i in &a {} NOT WORK
>    for i in a {}
>    for i in a {} // Error: Use moved value a
> }
> ```

but you can do:

```rust
fn main() {
  let a = 1..5;
  for i in a {} // implicitly calls into_iter()
  for i in a {} // implicitly calls into_iter()
}
```

